11:12.208 --> 11:14.375
Uh, representative?

11:14.375 --> 11:17.291
Rep-re-sen-ta-tive.

11:17.291 --> 11:18.625
Ask for a supervisor.

11:18.625 --> 11:19.834
The first one that picks up

11:19.834 --> 11:21.875
is always just
practicing English.

11:21.875 --> 11:23.458
Hello, Karishma.

11:23.458 --> 11:24.709
Yeah, I told you.

11:24.709 --> 11:27.417
JOAN: Yeah, well, somebody has
stolen my credit card numbers,

11:27.417 --> 11:29.583
and they’re making
bizarre purchases,

11:29.583 --> 11:31.959
and they’re sending them
to my house.

11:31.959 --> 11:33.000
Oh, yes.

11:33.000 --> 11:35.542
I’m quite sure
I did not purchase

11:35.542 --> 11:39.750
Lovin’ Lamb:
the Sexy Inflatable Sheep.

11:39.750 --> 11:42.125
Ask for a supervisor,
and then just yell at him.

11:42.125 --> 11:43.542
Oh, no, don’t transfer me,

11:43.542 --> 11:44.792
because I always
get disconnect--

11:44.792 --> 11:45.875
(line clicks)

11:45.875 --> 11:47.875
♪

11:47.875 --> 11:49.834
(phone beeps)

11:49.834 --> 11:51.667
Customer service?

11:51.667 --> 11:52.667
No, no.

11:52.667 --> 11:53.834
Fraud prevention?

11:54.709 --> 11:56.083
Human?

11:56.083 --> 11:57.875
Ask for a supervisor.

11:57.875 --> 11:59.208
Hu-man?

11:59.208 --> 12:01.458
Don’t transfer me!

12:01.458 --> 12:02.917
Don’t put me on hold!

12:02.917 --> 12:04.083
Oh, no, please don’t--

12:04.083 --> 12:05.083
(line clicks)

12:09.291 --> 12:11.125
I need a milkshake.

12:11.125 --> 12:12.959
Yeah. Get in the truck.

12:14.625 --> 12:15.792
JOAN: They said the wait time

12:15.792 --> 12:18.041
would be five minutes--
it’s been 15!

12:18.041 --> 12:19.709
You should’ve asked
for a supervisor.

12:22.667 --> 12:25.500
WOMAN:<i> Hello. Fraud prevention.</i>

12:25.500 --> 12:27.875
<i>With whom do I have</i>
<i>the pleasure of speaking today?</i>

12:27.875 --> 12:30.125
-Joan Short!
<i>-Hello?</i>

12:30.125 --> 12:31.834
Hi! I’m here!

12:31.834 --> 12:34.417
<i>-Is there anyone on the line?</i>
-I’m here!

12:34.417 --> 12:36.208
MAN:<i> Welcome to Big Joey’s!</i>

12:36.208 --> 12:38.291
-I’m here!
MAN:<i> Congratulations.</i>

12:38.291 --> 12:39.333
<i>Can I take your order?</i>

12:39.333 --> 12:41.542
She wants to talk
to the supervisor.

12:41.542 --> 12:42.709
MAN:<i> I am the supervisor,</i>

12:42.709 --> 12:44.125
<i>until Gary gets</i>
<i>out of the bathroom.</i>

12:44.125 --> 12:45.875
WOMAN:<i> Is there anyone there?</i>
MAN:<i> Yes!</i>

12:45.875 --> 12:46.792
-I’m here!
MAN:<i> I’m here!</i>

12:46.792 --> 12:48.834
<i>I’m ready for your order!</i>

12:48.834 --> 12:51.083
Ah, we--we’d like
a couple of Big Joeys,

12:51.083 --> 12:53.458
fries, and a vanilla milkshake.

12:53.458 --> 12:54.709
Can you hear me?

12:54.709 --> 12:55.875
WOMAN:<i> This is a bad connection.</i>

12:55.875 --> 12:57.417
<i>Can you try calling back</i>
<i>on a landline?</i>

12:57.417 --> 12:59.166
No. No, no, no.

12:59.166 --> 13:00.667
MAN:<i> $13.85, next window.</i>

13:02.083 --> 13:04.458
JOAN: I want my milkshake.

13:04.458 --> 13:06.333
JOHN: And you’re gonna get it.

13:06.333 --> 13:09.458
I got a couple of years
of console change here,

13:09.458 --> 13:10.417
and they gotta take it.

13:10.417 --> 13:11.750
I know my rights.

13:11.750 --> 13:13.125
-Here. There you go.
-Oh, boy.

13:13.125 --> 13:15.083
-Oh, boy, that’s oxidized.
-Oh.

13:15.083 --> 13:16.291
Oh. Sorry.

13:16.291 --> 13:17.834
There--that’s your tip,
down there.

13:17.834 --> 13:19.625
-Oh, jackpot. Great.
-Mhm, yeah.

13:19.625 --> 13:21.750
MAN: Okay, would you guys mind
pulling forward?

13:21.750 --> 13:23.959
It’s gonna take a few minutes
to count all this change.

13:23.959 --> 13:30.333
♪

13:30.333 --> 13:31.875
(indistinct chatter)

13:31.875 --> 13:33.625
So, some bad news:

13:33.625 --> 13:35.500
We just ran out of milkshakes.

13:35.500 --> 13:37.125
That baseball team
just cleaned us out.

13:37.125 --> 13:40.208
But, um, here is a diet soda

13:40.208 --> 13:43.125
and a free bottle
of Big Joey cologne.

13:43.125 --> 13:45.041
It’s called Eau de Joe.

13:45.041 --> 13:46.375
It keeps the bees away.

13:46.375 --> 13:47.542
Have a Big Joey day.

13:49.667 --> 13:51.583
-Joanie.
-Hey!

13:51.583 --> 13:53.625
Joanie.

13:53.625 --> 13:55.125
MAN: Ma’am, if you get
out of the car,

13:55.125 --> 13:57.709
I’m gonna have
to blow my whistle.

13:57.709 --> 14:01.166
JOAN: Today is not the day for
you to run out of milkshakes,

14:01.166 --> 14:05.041
because today,
I’ve had my identity stolen.

14:05.041 --> 14:07.250
I spent 23 minutes listening

14:07.250 --> 14:09.458
to a Muzak version
of Jimi Hendrix,

14:09.458 --> 14:12.458
and I was sent
an inflatable sex sheep.

14:12.458 --> 14:13.750
Ma’am, if you come any closer,

14:13.750 --> 14:15.208
I’m gonna have
to blow my whistle.

14:15.208 --> 14:17.542
Now you come out here,
and you tell me

14:17.542 --> 14:19.250
there are no more milkshakes?

14:19.250 --> 14:21.291
I’m afraid that won’t do.

14:21.291 --> 14:24.291
Joanie? Joanie,
I got your milkshake.

14:24.291 --> 14:25.333
(gasps)

14:28.875 --> 14:30.792
Hey, you kids know
the deal, huh?

14:30.792 --> 14:33.083
One mystery package
for each milkshake.

14:33.083 --> 14:35.125
No takebacks, no tradesies.

14:37.625 --> 14:39.125
(slurping)

14:39.125 --> 14:42.667
You really know
how to make a woman happy.

14:42.667 --> 14:44.208
Fraud prevention.

14:44.208 --> 14:45.667
Supervisor.

14:45.667 --> 14:47.500
♪

14:47.500 --> 14:50.375
Ah.

14:50.375 --> 14:51.792
(slurping)

14:54.333 --> 14:56.417
COLLEEN: You don’t care about
this ping-pong rivalry, do you?

14:56.417 --> 14:58.083
No. I’m an adult.

14:58.083 --> 14:59.458
I know how to let things go.

14:59.458 --> 15:01.834
♪

15:04.625 --> 15:07.291
♪

15:07.291 --> 15:09.083
COLLEEN:
I love Paris.

15:09.083 --> 15:10.250
MATT: Sometimes I think
people travel

15:10.250 --> 15:11.750
just so they can
talk about it later.

15:11.750 --> 15:14.000
TIM: That was a great trip.
Remember at that restaurant?

15:14.000 --> 15:15.667
You told the waiter
you had to take a crêpe.

15:15.667 --> 15:17.417
(laughing)

15:17.417 --> 15:18.875
TIM: You got to tell
that one at my funeral.

15:18.875 --> 15:20.041
Absolutely.

15:20.041 --> 15:21.875
Ooh, someone’s wedding!

15:21.875 --> 15:23.291
Jen, you look so pretty.

15:23.291 --> 15:24.709
-I love that dress.
-Thanks.

15:24.709 --> 15:26.333
Yeah, it’s Vera Wong.

15:26.333 --> 15:27.917
You mean Wang.

15:27.917 --> 15:28.667
No.

15:30.959 --> 15:33.041
Greg, your smile looks
a little weird here.

15:35.709 --> 15:37.917
JOAN:
Mm, no.

15:37.917 --> 15:40.834
No? Did I--
did I say something wrong?

15:40.834 --> 15:42.583
I’m actually not allowed
to answer that question.

15:42.583 --> 15:43.834
GREG: Oh, but I’d love
to hear the answer

15:43.834 --> 15:44.959
to that question, Matt.

15:44.959 --> 15:47.333
I’d love to hear the answer
to that particular question.

15:47.333 --> 15:48.709
Not much to tell.

15:48.709 --> 15:50.625
This ding-dong
and that ding-dong

15:50.625 --> 15:52.250
were being dum-dums.

15:52.250 --> 15:54.125
TIM: You don’t know this story?

15:54.125 --> 15:55.417
Oh, it’s awesome.

15:55.417 --> 15:57.083
GREG: Oh, yeah,
if attempted murder’s awesome.

15:57.083 --> 15:59.125
MATT: Oh, my--for the last time,
it slipped.

15:59.125 --> 16:01.125
HEATHER:
Okay, okay, okay.

16:01.125 --> 16:02.542
It’s the night
before the wedding,

16:02.542 --> 16:04.417
Greg and Matt are
playing ping-pong,

16:04.417 --> 16:06.625
game gets a little competitive,

16:06.625 --> 16:08.333
Greg gets hit in the face
with a paddle,

16:08.333 --> 16:10.333
and he loses a tooth.

16:10.333 --> 16:13.000
Or as he had to say
on our honeymoon,

16:13.000 --> 16:14.000
a "toof."

16:14.000 --> 16:15.000
(snickering)

16:15.000 --> 16:16.166
COLLEEN:
Did you just throw it at him?

16:16.166 --> 16:17.083
-No.
-Yes!

16:17.083 --> 16:18.000
MATT:
What? No.

16:18.000 --> 16:19.583
GREG: Oh, you knew that
you were about to lose.

16:19.583 --> 16:21.959
MATT: "About to lose,"
it was 19 to 20.

16:21.959 --> 16:23.250
You have to win by two.

16:23.250 --> 16:25.375
You know I was
about to beat you.

16:25.375 --> 16:26.417
Based on what evidence?

16:26.417 --> 16:27.750
The fact that
you’ve never beaten me

16:27.750 --> 16:29.208
at anything in your life ever?

16:29.208 --> 16:30.583
-That’s not true.
-That’s true.

16:30.583 --> 16:32.083
-No. No, that’s not true.
MATT: Greg.

16:32.083 --> 16:33.959
Will you two stop?

16:33.959 --> 16:35.792
I mean, my wedding photographs
were ruined

16:35.792 --> 16:37.583
because of this stupid
sibling rivalry.

16:37.583 --> 16:39.959
I mean, literally, he smiled
at me during the ceremony,

16:39.959 --> 16:41.792
I felt like I was
marrying a first grader.

16:41.792 --> 16:43.542
JOHN: Come on, guys,
it’s just a game.

16:43.542 --> 16:46.417
Says the man who takes only
the winner out to ice cream.

16:46.417 --> 16:48.583
The world is a hard place.

16:48.583 --> 16:50.125
COLLEEN: So did you guys ever
finish the game?

16:50.125 --> 16:51.041
HEATHER:
Oh, no, no, no, no, no.

16:51.041 --> 16:52.959
They have not played since.

16:52.959 --> 16:55.750
JOAN: You know, I think it might
be time to let this go.

16:55.750 --> 16:57.333
-Thank you.
-Oh, come on, Mom.

16:57.333 --> 16:59.625
Yes, you’re brothers.

16:59.625 --> 17:01.125
Tell each other
you love each other.

17:03.041 --> 17:04.583
I love you.

17:04.583 --> 17:05.667
JOAN: Oh, honey.

17:05.667 --> 17:07.583
-Look him in the eye.
-Come on.

17:10.125 --> 17:11.291
I love you.

17:11.291 --> 17:12.709
Yeah, see?

17:12.709 --> 17:14.125
Wasn’t that hard.

17:14.125 --> 17:16.500
-Loser.
TIM: Ooh, snack!

17:16.500 --> 17:17.667
HEATHER:
No, no, no.

17:17.667 --> 17:19.625
It--it’s "snap."

17:19.625 --> 17:23.083
TIM: Really? I’ve always
said "snack."

17:23.083 --> 17:25.166
COLLEEN: You don’t care about
this ping-pong rivalry, do you?

17:25.166 --> 17:27.333
What? No, I’m an adult.

17:27.333 --> 17:28.500
I know how to let things go.

17:29.709 --> 17:32.041
(clattering)

17:34.959 --> 17:37.375
Honey, we’ve got to get
the key back from Matt.

17:37.375 --> 17:44.083
♪

17:44.083 --> 17:46.458
My whole life. Hmm?

17:46.458 --> 17:48.959
I have never been better
than Matt at anything

17:48.959 --> 17:51.041
-except losing.
JEN: Honey.

17:51.041 --> 17:53.291
You are successful.

17:53.291 --> 17:54.625
You’re a great father.

17:54.625 --> 17:59.208
You have a beautiful,
intelligent, tolerant wife.

17:59.208 --> 18:01.542
You don’t need
this stupid ping-pong game

18:01.542 --> 18:02.750
to prove yourself.

18:02.750 --> 18:04.125
Oh, yes, I do.

18:04.125 --> 18:05.208
I need this.

18:05.208 --> 18:06.291
We need this.

18:06.291 --> 18:07.333
No, I don’t need this.

18:07.333 --> 18:09.750
GREG:
I really need you to need this.

18:09.750 --> 18:14.125
I just feel like my need
for you to "un-need" this

18:14.125 --> 18:17.041
is kind of trumping
your need to need it.

18:18.500 --> 18:19.875
Well, I’m glad
that we both understand

18:19.875 --> 18:20.917
that we both need this.

18:20.917 --> 18:21.917
♪

18:24.500 --> 18:30.125
♪

18:32.083 --> 18:33.667
MATT:
So, I see you got a headband.

18:33.667 --> 18:36.500
Oh, of course I have a headband.

18:36.500 --> 18:39.166
What do you use to help you
wear an exfoliating mask?

18:40.417 --> 18:41.542
All righty.

18:41.542 --> 18:42.917
Let’s do this.

18:42.917 --> 18:45.917
Somebody’s getting ice cream,
compliments of this guy.

18:45.917 --> 18:46.750
19-20.

18:49.458 --> 18:51.750
-You ready?
-Born ready.

18:51.750 --> 18:54.333
(both grunting)

18:54.333 --> 18:56.625
(Greg yipping)

19:02.208 --> 19:04.000
-Ah!
-Ah.

19:05.375 --> 19:06.667
20-20, just like my vision.

19:06.667 --> 19:08.333
Unlike some people,
I don’t need glasses.

19:08.333 --> 19:09.834
-I don’t wear glasses.
-Sure about that?

19:09.834 --> 19:11.792
You didn’t see that little ball
go zooming right past you.

19:11.792 --> 19:12.875
Stop trying to get in my head.

19:12.875 --> 19:14.792
MATT: I’m already there, buddy,
I live there.

19:14.792 --> 19:16.291
No, you live in this garage.

19:16.291 --> 19:18.083
TIM:
Ooh, snack!

19:18.083 --> 19:19.834
Snap. Shoot!

19:19.834 --> 19:22.792
♪

19:22.792 --> 19:24.291
(Greg yipping)

19:25.750 --> 19:28.000
GREG:
Ah!

19:28.000 --> 19:29.166
MATT:
So what’s that?

19:29.166 --> 19:30.125
Match point?

19:30.125 --> 19:32.041
-21-20?
-Yeah.

19:32.041 --> 19:34.291
(breathes deeply)

19:34.291 --> 19:35.500
I love you, baby.

19:35.500 --> 19:36.875
This one’s for Lark!

19:36.875 --> 19:39.041
"Love Theme, St. Elmo’s Fire"
<i>♪ Play the game ♪</i>

19:39.041 --> 19:41.917
<i>♪ You know you can’t quit</i>
<i>until it’s won ♪</i>

19:41.917 --> 19:45.375
♪

19:45.375 --> 19:46.792
<i>♪ Soldier on ♪</i>

19:46.792 --> 19:47.959
(both grunting)

19:47.959 --> 19:53.667
<i>♪ Only you can do</i>
<i>what must be done ♪</i>

19:53.667 --> 19:56.125
<i>♪ I can make it ♪</i>

19:56.125 --> 19:57.792
<i>♪ I know I can ♪</i>

19:57.792 --> 20:01.542
<i>♪ You broke the boy in me,</i>
<i>but you won’t break the man ♪</i>

20:01.542 --> 20:03.083
Yes.

20:03.083 --> 20:05.208
<i>-♪ I can see a new horizon ♪</i>
HEATHER: Yeah!

20:05.208 --> 20:07.333
<i>♪ Underneath the blazin’ sky ♪</i>

20:07.333 --> 20:12.500
<i>♪ Take me where my future’s</i>
<i>lyin’, St. Elmo’s fire ♪</i>

20:12.500 --> 20:14.709
-Oh!
-No!

20:14.709 --> 20:16.041
Yes!

20:16.041 --> 20:17.959
-Ow!
-Ooh!

20:17.959 --> 20:18.875
Oh!

20:20.083 --> 20:20.875
No.

20:23.542 --> 20:25.333
(spits)

20:27.291 --> 20:29.125
Please tell me that
was the fake one.

20:31.458 --> 20:34.291
It will be.

20:34.291 --> 20:36.750
I’m gonna go leave a message
on Dr. Frankel’s service.

20:36.750 --> 20:40.875
♪

20:40.875 --> 20:42.667
JEN: Is it--is it going?
GREG: Mhm.

20:42.667 --> 20:45.709
JEN:
Okay. Everybody smile.

20:45.709 --> 20:48.417
(camera shutter clicks)

20:48.417 --> 20:50.083
Well, there’s always next year.

20:50.083 --> 20:51.083
Yeah.

20:52.208 --> 20:59.125
♪
